mourned a man whom many viewed as the savior of the united states he was buried 
in oak ridge cemetery in springfield where a one seven seven foot five four m 
tall granite tomb surmounted with several bronze statues of lincoln was 
constructed by one eight seven four to prevent repeated attempts to steal 
